# Translations

Rules in this section apply to files under **`src/locales`**.

## Where to define translations

- **Define all translation JSON files under the `src/locales` directory.** Use one directory per locale (e.g. `src/locales/en/`, `src/locales/fr/`).
- **Key naming:** Use **camelCase** for keys (e.g. `loading`, `saveDraft`, `validationError`).
- Keep keys stable across locales so code can reference the same key in every language.

## Common words namespace

- Use `words.json` file for common, reusable **singular words** only (e.g. `healthy`, `error`, `success`, `loading`, `save`, `cancel`).
- Do not put full phrases or sentence-style strings in `words.json`; use other namespaces for those.

## Structure of `words.json`

